claim.claim-text:
A power supply circuit comprising:
first and second power supply lines (LH1, LL1) that are connected to an inductive load (21);
an input line (L1, L2) that is connected to an alternating-current power supply (E1);
a first conversion section (11) that converts, into a first direct-current voltage, an alternating-current voltage input from said input line, and applies said first direct-current voltage between said first and said second power supply lines, said first power supply line being employed as a positive pole;

a diode (D1) that has a cathode and an anode, and is arranged between said first and said second power supply lines such that said anode faces toward said first power supply line side;
a capacitor (C1) that has both ends connected to a direct-current load (22), and is connected in series with said diode between said first and said second power supply lines;
a switch section (S1) that is provided on said input line, and selects conduction/non-conduction between said alternating-current power supply and said first conversion section; and
a second conversion section (12) that converts, into a second direct-current voltage, said alternating-current voltage input without passing through said switch section, and is connected to a connection point (P1) located between said capacitor and said diode to apply said second direct-current voltage to said capacitor.
